ach other making the clump undetectable in the\nspectral energy distribution and visibilities. The lack of infrared brightening\nduring the 'Great Dimming' therefore does not exclude extinction due to a dust\nclump as one of the possible mechanisms. The visibilities can be reproduced by\na spherical wind with dust condensing at 13 stellar radii and a dust mass-loss\nrate of (2.1 - 4.9) $\\times$ 10$^{-10}$ $\\mathit{M}_{\\odot} {\\rm yr}^{-1}$,\nhowever, in order to reproduce the complexity of the observed closure phases,\nadditional surface features or dust clumps would be needed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Mar 2023 19:24:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-17"}
