al volumes of a few Mpcs, closest AGN, Star-Burst or very close SNR are\nsuperimposing their signals, frozen in different epochs, distances and\ndirections, feeding small and wide anisotropy. Possible tests to confirm, or\nuntangle the current model from alternative ones, are suggested and updated.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Mar 2023 20:39:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-24"}
